<p>A button that can be pressed by the user. Event handlers can be used to trap mouse, keyboard and other events. It is typically rendered as a grey outset rectangle. You can specify the label of the button using the <span class="script">template.XULAttr("label")</span> attribute or by placing content inside the button.</p>
<p>More information is available in the <a title="en/XUL_Tutorial/Adding_Buttons" href="/en/XUL_Tutorial/Adding_Buttons">XUL tutorial</a>.</p>
